": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triple_conjunction"}
{"title_page": "Kitemark", "text_new": "{{third-party|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox certification mark\n| name           = Kitemark\n| image          = [[Image:BSI Kitemark.svg|120px]]\n| caption        = BSI Kitemark certification symbol\n| expansion      = \n| agency         = [[BSI Group]]\n| region         = [[United Kingdom]]\n| founded        = 1903\n| defunct        =\n| predecessor    = \n| successor      = \n| products       = Various\n| legalstatus    = Advisory\n| mandatorysince = \n| homepage       = {{URL|www.bsigroup.com/en-GB/kitemark/|Kitemark home page}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Kitemark''' is a UK product and [[service quality]] [[trade mark]] which is owned and operated by The British Standards Institution ([[BSI Group]]).\n\nThe Kitemark is most frequently used to identify products where safety is paramount, such as crash helmets, smoke alarms and flood defences. In recent years the Kitemark has also been applied to a range of services, such as electrical installations; car servicing and accident repair; and window installations.\n\n== Origins of the Kitemark ==\nThe Kitemark was originally conceived in 1903<ref name=\"history\">Robert C McWilliam. ''BSI: The first hundred years''. 2001. Thanet Press. London</ref> as a symbol to identify products manufactured to meet [[British Standards]]' specifications. \"Kitemark\" came from the kite shape of the graphic device which was drawn up \u2013 an uppercase B (for British) on its back, over an S (for standard), enclosed by a V (for verification).<ref name=\"Where did the BSI Kitemark TM Originate?\">[https://www.bsigroup.com/LocalFiles/EN-AU/documents-/Kitemark.pdf \"Where did the BSI Kitemark TM Originate?\"]</ref>\n\nThe Kitemark was subsequently registered as a trade mark on 12 June 1903<ref name=\"history\"/> and as such is among the oldest product quality marks in the world still in regular use.{{fact|date=April 2016}}yes132 jy[ kay\n\n== History ==\nThe Kitemark was initially used as a trade mark on tramway rails in 1903 and was instrumental in reducing the number of specifications for rails from 75 to 5.<ref name=\"history\"/> The first full Kitemark scheme \u2013 equivalent to today\u2019s Kitemark \u2013 came into being in 1926, when the [[General Electric Company]] was awarded a Kitemark for light fittings.<ref name=\"history\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/money/2009/feb/27/condom-testing-kitemark |title=Rising to the Kitemark challenge |last=Tran |first=Mark |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=27 February 2009 |accessdate=16 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nFor the next few decades, the use of Kitemark was largely limited to technical and engineering applications up until the 1950s when the boom in consumer products led to increased concern about product safety. By the 1960s the Kitemark was being used to identify safe products in areas such as nightwear, domestic furniture, pressure cookers and motorcycle helmets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsigroup.com/en/About-BSI/About-BSI-Group/BSI-History/|title=Standards, Training, Testing, Assessment and Certification - BSI Group|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nWith the introduction of quality management systems standards in the 1970s Kitemark schemes were developed in areas such as double glazing and fire safety. Today there are more than 450 individual Kitemark schemes covering products as diverse as printed circuit boards and cattle tags, and services as disparate as financial products and flood protection.\n\n== Availability ==\nThe Kitemark is only available from [[BSI Group]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsigroup.com|title=Standards, Training, Testing, Assessment and Certification - BSI Group|publisher=}}</ref> To obtain Kitemark certification, products and services are assessed by BSI Product Services to ensure that they meet the requirements of the relevant British, European, trade association or international specification or standard. In addition, delivery of the product or service is audited against an accredited quality management system. Once a Kitemark licence is issued, licensees are regularly audited and are subject to surveillance visits to ensure continuing compliance.\n\n== Market acceptance ==\nThe Kitemark is not a legal requirement, but is often used as a point of differentiation in competitive markets<ref>{{cite web |title=Differentiate your business with BSI Kitemark |url=https://www.bsigroup.com/en-GB/kitemark/ |website=www.bsigroup.com |publisher=BSI Group |accessdate=25 September 2019}}</ref> and is widely trusted: a 2006 survey demonstrated that the Kitemark is recognized by 82 per cent of the UK population, 88 per cent of whom trust the Kitemark, 93 per cent of whom believe that Kitemark products are safer, and 91 per cent of whom believe the product is of a better quality than similar products without the Kitemark.<ref>GfK NOP Consumer Survey July 2006</ref> A 2008 [[YouGov]] poll showed that almost half (49 per cent) of UK consumers look for a Kitemark when making a purchase.<ref name=soars>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.co.uk/cgi/news/release?id=250139|title=Kitemark Soars 100 Places in Leading Brands Survey /PR Newswire UK/|first=BSI Product|last=Services|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008 and 2009 the Kitemark was independently voted a Superbrand in the Top 500 Business Superbrands in the UK.<ref name=soars/>\n\n== Examples of Kitemark schemes ==\n* Building Information Modelling (BIM)\n* Balustrading\n* Car accident repair\n* Car servicing\n* Carbon monoxide detectors\n* Customer service\n* Fire extinguishers\n* Windows and doors\n* Glass\n* Plugs and sockets\n* Prophylactics\n* Motorcycle helmets\n* Horse riding helmets\n* Ladders\n* Flood barriers\n\n== Misuse of \"Kitemark\" ==\nThe word \"Kitemark\" is a [[registered trade mark]] of the British Standards Institution. BSI, owner of the name and trade mark, takes protection of the mark extremely seriously and action is taken where misuse or infringement occurs.<ref>[http://www.businessstandards.com/In_Brief/071025_BS21_Kitemark Kitemark: Keeping track, ''Business Standards'', October 2007<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[BSI Group]]\n* [[British Standards]]\n* [[CE marking]]\n* [[Product certification]]\n* [[Certification mark]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.kitemark.com www.kitemark.com]\n* [http://www.bsigroup.com www.bsigroup.com]\n\n[[Category:Consumer symbols]]\n[[Category:Product safety]]\n[[Category:Trademarks]]\n", "text_old": "{{third-party|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox certification mark\n| name           = Kitemark\n| image          = [[Image:BSI Kitemark.svg|120px]]\n| caption        = BSI Kitemark certification symbol\n| expansion      = \n| agency         = [[BSI Group]]\n| region         = [[United Kingdom]]\n| founded        = 1903\n| defunct        =\n| predecessor    = \n| successor      = \n| products       = Various\n| legalstatus    = Advisory\n| mandatorysince = \n| homepage       = {{URL|www.bsigroup.com/en-GB/kitemark/|Kitemark home page}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Kitemark''' is a UK product and [[service quality]] [[trade mark]] which is owned and operated by The British Standards Institution ([[BSI Group]]).\n\nThe Kitemark is most frequently used to identify products where safety is paramount, such as crash helmets, smoke alarms and flood defences. In recent years the Kitemark has also been applied to a range of services, such as electrical installations; car servicing and accident repair; and window installations.\n\n== Origins of the Kitemark ==\nThe Kitemark was originally conceived in 1903<ref name=\"history\">Robert C McWilliam. ''BSI: The first hundred years''. 2001. Thanet Press. London</ref> as a symbol to identify products manufactured to meet [[British Standards]]' specifications. \"Kitemark\" came from the kite shape of the graphic device which was drawn up \u2013 an uppercase B (for British) on its back, over an S (for standard), enclosed by a V (for verification).<ref name=\"Where did the BSI Kitemark TM Originate?\">[https://www.bsigroup.com/LocalFiles/EN-AU/documents-/Kitemark.pdf \"Where did the BSI Kitemark TM Originate?\"]</ref>\n\nThe Kitemark was subsequently registered as a trade mark on 12 June 1903<ref name=\"history\"/> and as such is among the oldest product quality marks in the world still in regular use.{{fact|date=April 2016}}\n\n== History ==\nThe Kitemark was initially used as a trade mark on tramway rails in 1903 and was instrumental in reducing the number of specifications for rails from 75 to 5.<ref name=\"history\"/> The first full Kitemark scheme \u2013 equivalent to today\u2019s Kitemark \u2013 came into being in 1926, when the [[General Electric Company]] was awarded a Kitemark for light fittings.<ref name=\"history\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/money/2009/feb/27/condom-testing-kitemark |title=Rising to the Kitemark challenge |last=Tran |first=Mark |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=27 February 2009 |accessdate=16 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nFor the next few decades, the use of Kitemark was largely limited to technical and engineering applications up until the 1950s when the boom in consumer products led to increased concern about product safety. By the 1960s the Kitemark was being used to identify safe products in areas such as nightwear, domestic furniture, pressure cookers and motorcycle helmets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsigroup.com/en/About-BSI/About-BSI-Group/BSI-History/|title=Standards, Training, Testing, Assessment and Certification - BSI Group|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nWith the introduction of quality management systems standards in the 1970s Kitemark schemes were developed in areas such as double glazing and fire safety. Today there are more than 450 individual Kitemark schemes covering products as diverse as printed circuit boards and cattle tags, and services as disparate as financial products and flood protection.\n\n== Availability ==\nThe Kitemark is only available from [[BSI Group]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsigroup.com|title=Standards, Training, Testing, Assessment and Certification - BSI Group|publisher=}}</ref> To obtain Kitemark certification, products and services are assessed by BSI Product Services to ensure that they meet the requirements of the relevant British, European, trade association or international specification or standard. In addition, delivery of the product or service is audited against an accredited quality management system. Once a Kitemark licence is issued, licensees are regularly audited and are subject to surveillance visits to ensure continuing compliance.\n\n== Market acceptance ==\nThe Kitemark is not a legal requirement, but is often used as a point of differentiation in competitive markets<ref>{{cite web |title=Differentiate your business with BSI Kitemark |url=https://www.bsigroup.com/en-GB/kitemark/ |website=www.bsigroup.com |publisher=BSI Group |accessdate=25 September 2019}}</ref> and is widely trusted: a 2006 survey demonstrated that the Kitemark is recognized by 82 per cent of the UK population, 88 per cent of whom trust the Kitemark, 93 per cent of whom believe that Kitemark products are safer, and 91 per cent of whom believe the product is of a better quality than similar products without the Kitemark.<ref>GfK NOP Consumer Survey July 2006</ref> A 2008 [[YouGov]] poll showed that almost half (49 per cent) of UK consumers look for a Kitemark when making a purchase.<ref name=soars>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.co.uk/cgi/news/release?id=250139|title=Kitemark Soars 100 Places in Leading Brands Survey /PR Newswire UK/|first=BSI Product|last=Services|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008 and 2009 the Kitemark was independently voted a Superbrand in the Top 500 Business Superbrands in the UK.<ref name=soars/>\n\n== Examples of Kitemark schemes ==\n* Building Information Modelling (BIM)\n* Balustrading\n* Car accident repair\n* Car servicing\n* Carbon monoxide detectors\n* Customer service\n* Fire extinguishers\n* Windows and doors\n* Glass\n* Plugs and sockets\n* Prophylactics\n* Motorcycle helmets\n* Horse riding helmets\n* Ladders\n* Flood barriers\n\n== Misuse of \"Kitemark\" ==\nThe word \"Kitemark\" is a [[registered trade mark]] of the British Standards Institution. BSI, owner of the name and trade mark, takes protection of the mark extremely seriously and action is taken where misuse or infringement occurs.<ref>[http://www.businessstandards.com/In_Brief/071025_BS21_Kitemark Kitemark: Keeping track, ''Business Standards'', October 2007<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[BSI Group]]\n* [[British Standards]]\n* [[CE marking]]\n* [[Product certification]]\n* [[Certification mark]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.kitemark.com www.kitemark.com]\n* [http://www.bsigroup.com www.bsigroup.com]\n\n[[Category:Consumer symbols]]\n[[Category:Product safety]]\n[[Category:Trademarks]]\n", "name_user": "188.30.148.98", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Undid revision 953842316 byJohn Maynard Friedman(talk),unexplained removal)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kitemark"}
{"title_page": "NoCopyrightSounds", "text_new": "{{pp-pc|small=yes}}\n{{short description|British record label}}\n{{Infobox record label\n| name = NoCopyrightSounds\n| genre = {{hlist|[[House music|House]]|[[dubstep]]|[[Trap music (EDM)|trap]]|[[drum and bass]]|[[electropop]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ncsmusic.com/ |title=NCS |website=ncsmusic.com |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>}}\n| founder = Billy Woodford\n| image = No Copyright Sounds logo.jpg\n| website = {{url|ncsmusic.com}}\n| founded = August 2011<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://routenote.com/blog/exclusive-interview-billy-woodford-founder-of-nocopyrightsounds-ncs/ |title=Exclusive Interview: Billy Woodford Founder of NoCopyrightSounds (NCS) - RouteNote Blog |date=2015-03-27 |website=RouteNote Blog |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n| location = [[Manchester]], United Kingdom\n| module = {{Infobox YouTube|embed=yes\n| name = NoCopyrightSounds\n| pseudonym = \n| years_active = 2011\u2013present\n| genre = [[Music]]\n| subscribers = 24.7 million\n| views = 7.2 billion\n| stats_update = 24 January 2020\n<!--Current general consensus says to update every hundred thousand subscribers and every hundred million views. Please also update the stats_update date if you update stats.-->\n| network = \n| associated_acts = \n| catchphrase(s) = \n| silver_button = yes\n| silver_year = 2013\n| gold_button = yes\n| gold_year = 2014\n| diamond_button = yes\n| diamond_year = 2017\n| ruby_button = \n| ruby_year =\n}}\n}}\n\n'''NoCopyrightSounds''' ('''NCS''') is a British record label that releases royalty-free [[electronic dance music]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.edmsauce.com/2017/11/09/copyright-free-music/ |title=Copyright Free Music: These Labels Are Changing Up Royalty Free Music |last=Stevo |date=2017-11-09 |website=EDM Sauce |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref> Starting as a [[YouTube]] channel,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/nocopyrightsounds.co.uk/ncs|title=FAQ / Usage Policy|website=NoCopyrightSounds|access-date=16 February 2019}}</ref> it reached 1 million paid downloads in 2017.<ref name=\"YEDM1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.youredm.com/2017/12/31/nocopyrightsounds-hits-huge-milestone-1-million-digital-sales/ |title=This EDM Label Just Hit 1 Million Sales Despite Giving Away Its Music Free |date=2017-12-31 |website=Your EDM |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nNoCopyrightSounds was started as a YouTube channel in 2011 by an \"avid gamer\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://startups.co.uk/young-entrepreneurs-billy-woodford-nocopyrightsounds/ |title=Young Entrepreneurs: Billy Woodford, NoCopyrightSounds |date=2015-03-18 |website=Startups.co.uk: Starting a business advice and business ideas |language=en-GB |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref> named Billy Woodford.<ref name=\"YEDM1\"/><ref name=\"BB\"/> The label was described by ''[[Forbes]]'' as \"a YouTube-first label that allows indie creators to use and even monetize its music freely as long as they give due credit back to the content owners.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/cheriehu/2017/10/25/how-youtube-entrepreneurs-in-their-20s-are-disrupting-traditional-record-labels/#5a36e540182a |title=How YouTube Entrepreneurs In Their 20s Are Disrupting Traditional Record Labels |last=Hu |first=Cherie |website=Forbes |language=en |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.influencerupdate.biz/news/66698/nocopyrightsounds-youtube-channel-has-138m-subscribers-and-1m-paid-itunes-downloads/ |title=NoCopyrightSounds has 13.8m subscribers... and 1m paid iTunes downloads |website=influencerupdate.biz |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://weraveyou.com/2017/12/ncs-1-million-paid-downloads/ |title=Alan Walker's success is owed to this label and it just reached a major milestone |date=2017-12-18 |website=We Rave You |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, NoCopyrightSounds achieved a milestone of over a million sales of digital downloads, despite releasing music for free. The label manager Daniel J. Lee said \"Similar to services with a freemium model, NCS provides both the option to enjoy music for free but at the same time also enables fans to support the music across paid services\", asserting that the label releases music for free and also sells them.<ref name=\"BB\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8070591/ncs-label-free-music-1-million-paid-downloads |title=NCS Celebrates 1 Million Paid Downloads, Despite Giving Music Away for Free: Exclusive |website=Billboard |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref> Woodford, about the milestone, stated, \"I\u2019m immensely proud to have reached 1 million paid downloads, and believe this shows the growth and strength NCS has built over the years.\"<ref name=\"YEDM1\"/> He also commented that \"The demand for fresh original music from Creators is enormous and growing daily.\"<ref name=\"DA\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dancingastronaut.com/2017/12/youtube-record-label-nocopyrightsounds-hits-milestone-1-million-record-sales-despite-free-downloads/ |title=YouTube record label NCS hits $1 million in sales |date=2017-12-17 |website=Dancing Astronaut |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.edmsauce.com/2017/12/15/nocopyrightsounds-million-sales/ |title=Popular YouTube Label Reaches One Million Sales Despite Offering Free Downloads |last=Stevo |date=2017-12-15 |website=EDM Sauce |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n\nAs of February 2020, the label has received over 25 million subscribers on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|title=NoCopyrightSounds|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/NoCopyrightSounds|website=Youtube|accessdate=July 21, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"DA\"/><ref name=\"YEDM2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.youredm.com/2017/08/04/egzod-wake-feat-chris-linton-no-copyright-sounds/ |title=EGZOD - Wake Up (feat. Chris Linton) [NO COPYRIGHT SOUNDS] |date=2017-08-04 |website=Your EDM |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n\n==Artists==\n{{dynamic list}}\n<!-- Artist's last names, even as their stage names, take priority in alphabetical sorts like this. Please do not change this order without prior consensus on the Talk page. -->\n{{div col|colwidth=15em|gap=2em|content=\n*[[K-391]]<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Ahrix<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*3rd Prototype<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://shiningbeats.pl/3rd-prototype-powraca/ |title=3rd Prototype zn\u00f3w jest duetem! Niespodziewany zwrot akcji przypiecz\u0119towany nowym singlem |date=2019-08-14 |website=Shining Beats |language=pl-PL |access-date=2019-11-04 |trans-title=3rd Prototype is a duo again! An unexpected twist sealed with a new single}}</ref>\n*[[Aero Chord]]<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n<!--Artists listed here are listed in alphabetical order with last names taking priority where necessary. Alan Walker is therefore listed further down and should not be placed here.-->\n*Axol<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Beatcore<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Matthew Blake<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Cartoon<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Codeko<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*C\u00f8de<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Jo Cohen<ref name=\"BWW\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/NCS-The-Best-of-2016-Out-Now-on-NCS-20161220 |title='NCS: The Best of 2016' Out Now on NCS |last=Desk |first=BWW News |language=en |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n*[[Syn Cole]]<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Curbi<ref name=\"ITU2\"/>\n*Deaf Kev<ref name=\"ITU5\">{{Cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/ncs-the-best-of-2015/1069486392 |title=NCS: The Best of 2015 by Various Artists on Apple Music |date=2015-12-18 |language=en-CA |access-date=2018-01-26}}{{unreliable source?|date=November 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Debris (DJ)|Debris]]<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Defqwop<ref name=\"ITU4\"/>\n*Desembra<ref name=\"ITU4\"/>\n*Desmeon<ref name=\"ITU5\"/>\n*Diamond Eyes<ref name=\"ITU3\"/>\n*Different Heaven<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Dirty Dropouts {{small|(formerly Dropouts)}}<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Disfigure<ref name=\"ITU5\"/>\n*Distrion<ref name=\"ITU2\"/>\n*Diviners<ref name=\"ITU5\"/>\n*Droptek<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youredm.com/2019/11/29/your-edm-premiere-droptek-new-style-ncs/ |title=Your EDM Premiere: Droptek - New Style [NCS] |last=Meadow |first=Matthew |date=2019-11-29 |website=Your EDM |language=en-US |access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n*Egzod<ref name=\"YEDM2\"/>\n*William Ekh<ref name=\"ITU2\"/>\n*Electric Joy Ride<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Electro-Light<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Elektronomia<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dancingastronaut.com/2017/09/elektronomia-disco-boy-original-mix/ |title=Elektronomia - Disco Boy (Original Mix) - Dancing Astronaut |date=2017-09-17 |website=Dancing Astronaut |language=en-US |access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n*ElementD<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Exit Friendzone<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Paul Flint<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Floatinurboat<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Futuristik<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Glude<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Halcyon<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*High Maintenance<ref name=\"ITU5\"/>\n*Inukshuk<ref name=\"ITU5\"/>\n*Itro<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Izecold<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Janji<ref name=\"ITU5\"/>\n*JPB<ref name=\"BWW\"/>\n*Kasger<ref name=\"ITU5\"/>\n*Killercats<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Kontinuum<ref name=\"ITU4\"/>\n*Koven<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youredm.com/2018/12/04/koven-never-have-i-felt-this/ |title=Koven - Never Have I Felt This [NCS] |last=Simko |first=Darren |date=2018-12-04 |website=Your EDM |language=en-US |access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>\n*LarsM<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Last Heroes<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.edmsauce.com/2018/07/26/nurko-last-heroes-promise-me-feat-jessie-chambers/ |title=Nurko & Last Heroes - Promise Me (feat. Jessie Chambers) |last=Dylan |first=Charles |date=2018-07-27 |website=EDM Sauce |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-18}}</ref>\n*Lensko<ref name=\"ITU1\"/>\n*Chris Linton<ref name=\"BB\"/>\n*Lost Sky<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youredm.com/2018/08/03/lost-sky-teams-up-with-ncs-on-atmospheri