s, e.g. \"\u00a311.6 million\" not \"\u00a311,586,221\")-->\n}}\n'''''Monsoon''''' is a 2014 Canadian documentary film by [[Sturla Gunnarsson]] about the [[monsoon]] weather system [[Climate in India|in India]].\n\nThe film was shot in India in the extra-high-definition [[4K resolution|4K format]]<ref name=\"Variety-review\"/> with [[Red Digital Cinema Camera Company#Red Epic|Red Epic]] cameras.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.monsoonmovie.com/about/ |title=Production Notes |accessdate=2015-01-19 |work=Monsoon movie (official site)}}</ref>\n\nThe film was included in the list of [[Canada's Top Ten]] feature films of 2014, selected by a panel of filmmakers and industry professionals organized by TIFF.<ref>{{cite press release |title=TIFF Tips Its Toque to the Best in Canadian Filmmaking: Cronenberg, Dolan, and Gunnarson Among Directors Recognized |date=1 December 2014   |url=http://media.tiff.net.s3.amazonaws.com/content/pdf/14th_Annual_Canadas_Top_Ten_Film_Festival_2014.pdf   |publisher=TIFF }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |newspaper=Toronto Star |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2014/12/01/tiffs_top_ten_film_festival_spotlight_on_canadian_film.html |date=1 December 2014 |accessdate=21 December 2014 |author=Linda Barnard |title=TIFF\u2019s Top Ten Film Festival: Spotlight on Canadian film  }}</ref> Subsequently the film finished first in the audience balloting, of the features in \"Canada's Top Ten\".<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://d12gbu3zt5gvms.cloudfront.net/docs/y8JRNP_Award_Winners_Canada%27s_Top_Ten_Film_Festival_8513913_1421100000.pdf |publisher=tiff. |title=Sturla Gunnarsson\u2019s Monsoon crowned Canada's Top Ten Film Festival People\u2019s Choice Award winner |date=2015-01-12 }}</ref><ref name=\"Star-winner\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2015/01/12/monsoon_canadas_top_ten_peoples_choice_winner.html |newspaper=Toronto Star |title=Monsoon Canada\u2019s Top Ten people\u2019s choice winner |date=2015-01-12 |accessdate=2015-01-19 |author=Linda Barnard    }}</ref>\n\nThe film had a theatrical run in 2015;<ref name=\"Star-winner\"/> meanwhile Gunnarsson was quoted as being in discussions with an American distributor, following ''Monsoon'''s United States premiere at the 2015 [[Palm Springs International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Hadani Ditmars |date=2015-01-12 |accessdate=2015-01-19 |work=Macleans |url=http://www.macleans.ca/culture/movies/cancon-had-such-a-special-place-in-the-heart-of-palm-springs/ |title=Who knew CanCon had a special place in the heart of Palm Springs?  }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.monsoonmovie.com}}\n*{{IMDb title|id=tt3945988|title=Monsoon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Monsoon}}\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:Canadian documentary films]]\n[[Category:Canadian films]]\n[[Category:Foreign films shot in India]]\n[[Category:Rain]]\n[[Category:Climate of India]]\n[[Category:Weather events in India]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about India]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about environmental issues]]\n\n\n{{2010s-Canada-film-stub}}\n{{environment-documentary-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Monsoon\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| film name      = <!--(for non-English films: film's name in its native language)-->\n| director       = [[Sturla Gunnarsson]]\n| producer       = [[Ina Fichman]]\n| writer         = <!-- or: | writers = -->\n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{based on |[title of the original work] |[writer of the original work]}} -->\n| starring       = \n| narrator       = <!-- or: | narrators = -->\n| music          = [[Andrew T. MacKay]]\n| cinematography = [[Van Royko]]\n| editing        = [[Nick Hector]]\n\n| studio         = [[Intuitive Pictures]], [[Point du Jour]], and [[Monsoon Ontario]]<ref name=\"Variety-review\">{{cite web |url=https://